1. Definitions

"Software" means the Sift source code, documentation, assets, configuration,
and related materials distributed with this repository.

"You" means any individual or legal entity receiving, using, copying, modifying,
or distributing the Software.

"Hosted Service" means making the Software, a modified version of the Software,
or a substantially similar derivative available to third parties over a network,
including as SaaS, a managed service, a hosted product, an API service, or a
white-label service.

"Internal Use" means use by You, Your employees, contractors, or collaborators
for Your own personal, educational, research, evaluation, development, or
internal organizational purposes, where the Software is not offered as a Hosted
Service to third parties.

